causing massive anterior mediastinal haemorrhage, mimicking yet another cardiac 
rupture, 2 months later, followed, at the same admission, 2 weeks later, by 
sternal reconstruction for dehisced and infected sternum using pedicled 
myocutaneous latissimus dorsi flap. 5 years after the latissimus myoplasty, the 
patient remains in NYHA class 1 and is leading a normal life.

