Barea M(1), Cesana G.

Author information:
(1)Universidad Autonoma, Madrid, Spain. maite.barea@unam.es

One of the greatest problems of European societies is the financial 
sustainability of social protection systems in Europe. Together with Japan, 
Europe has the highest levels of ageing population in the world. This concern 
explains the reiterated insistence of the European Commission and the OECD 
regarding the reforms that governments should undertake. In this paper, 
reference is made to two of these reforms: prolonging of working life and a 
greater participation of women in the labour market.

